conversation.userMessage: I am planning a trip to Paris and I want to know what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack what to pack for my journey in June with my family.

agentResponse.reply:
• Paris in June: Warm days (20-25°C), mild nights (12-15°C) (Open-Meteo)
• Pack: Light clothing, raincoat (for occasional showers), comfortable walking shoes
• Family-friendly attractions:
  - Disneyland Paris: Theme park with rides and shows suitable for all ages
  - Louvre Museum: Offers kids' audio guides and family workshops
  - Luxembourg Garden: Large public park with playgrounds and puppet shows
